      {
        "paragraph_index": 3,
        "text": "### Key Notes\n\n- **Only two species** are reported: the mono-ammine [Ag(NH₃)]⁺ and the di-ammine [Ag(NH₃)₂]⁺. Higher complexes (tri-, tetra-) are not present in SRD-46.\n- All measurements are at **25 °C**; ionic strength spans 0–5 M across 16 different reference equilibrium networks (various media such as KNO₃, NaClO₄).\n- The constants are defined for **free NH₃** (the unprotonated form, pKₐ = 9.26), not total ammonia — important when working at lower pH.\n- The spread in log β values (e.g., β₂ from 7.14 to 8.18) reflects ionic-strength dependence: higher ionic strength generally lowers the apparent constant.",
